# ▶️ How to Run the Project

Follow these steps to run the Mini GPT project on your system.

---

## 📌 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/mini-gpt.git
cd mini-gpt
```

---

## 📌 2. Create Virtual Environment

```bash
python -m venv venv
```

### Activate Environment

#### Mac/Linux:

```bash
source venv/bin/activate
```

#### Windows:

```bash
venv\Scripts\activate
```

---

## 📌 3. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install torch streamlit datasets numpy==1.26.4
```

---

## 📌 4. Train the Model

```bash
python train.py
```

👉 This will:

* Load dataset
* Train the GPT model
* Save trained weights as `model.pt`

---

## 📌 5. Run the Streamlit App

```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

---

## 📌 6. Open in Browser

After running the above command, open:

```text
http://localhost:8501
```

---

## ⚠️ Important Notes

* Make sure `model.pt` exists before running the app
* If you face NumPy errors, ensure version:

```bash
pip install numpy==1.26.4
```

* Use simple prompts (word-level model)

---

## 🧪 Example Prompt

```text
the meaning of life
```

---

## 🛑 Troubleshooting

### Issue: Model not loading

👉 Run training again:

```bash
python train.py
```

### Issue: NumPy error

```bash
pip install numpy==1.26.4
```

### Issue: Slow training

👉 Reduce model size in `train.py`

---

## 🎯 Done!

You now have a working Mini GPT running locally 🚀
